Project: Rebuild Paradise Auto Detailing Website as Lightweight Static HTML/CSS/JS Site

Current site:
https://pas-detailing.com/

Goal:
Rebuild the existing WordPress website into a lightweight, fast, responsive, mobile-first HTML/CSS/JavaScript website for Paradise Auto Detailing. The finished site should be simple to maintain, quick to load, easy to host, and structured around the detailing service catalog, booking workflow, invoicing flow, customer intake expectations, Instagram gallery, and Google review visibility.

The site should not depend on WordPress, page builders, heavy frontend frameworks, or unnecessary JavaScript libraries. Build with semantic HTML, modern CSS, and minimal vanilla JavaScript unless there is a strong reason to use a build tool.

Primary Business Goals:
1. Present Paradise Auto Detailing’s service packages clearly.
2. Make it easy for customers to choose a package or request a quote.
3. Support Square Appointments as the likely booking/invoicing hook.
4. Provide clear policy/service terms around pricing, requotes, biohazard limitations, deposits, cancellations, and customer responsibilities.
5. Embed Instagram content as a visual gallery and encourage users to follow Paradise Auto Detailing.
6. Add Google Reviews visibility or a low-maintenance reviews section.
7. Make the site extremely mobile-friendly for customers browsing from phones.

Design Requirements:
- Mobile-first layout.
- Fast load times.
- Clean, premium auto-detailing aesthetic.
- Strong calls to action: Book Now, Text Us, Call Us, Request Quote, Follow on Instagram.
- Avoid clutter.
- Use service cards, comparison tables, and collapsible FAQ sections.
- Keep content easy to scan on mobile.
- Use compressed images and modern formats where possible.
- Use accessible contrast, readable font sizes, and large tap targets.
- Use semantic HTML landmarks: header, nav, main, section, footer.
- Include alt text for all meaningful images.
- Use no tracking scripts unless specifically approved by the client.

